<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Canonize" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Canonize,</orth> to make a saint of, to receive into the number of saints: <cit><quote>--d and worshipped as a saint,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.177" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 177</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.52.177" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.3.63" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 3, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.4.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 4, 47</bibl>.* == to glorify in general: <cit><quote>and fame in time to come c. us,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 2.2.202" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 2, 202</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>